# Memory

Ephemeral team-shared scratch. Mid-session decisions, running TODOs, open questions — anything Claude or the team needs to remember between turns but isn't yet a stable doc.

## What lives here

* Open questions still being worked.
* Decisions too small to be an ADR but too load-bearing to lose.
* Running TODOs the next session should pick up.
* Notes about *context* that don't belong in code or docs yet.

## What doesn't

* **Stable knowledge** — that's [Project Memory](../docs/) (architecture, ADRs, runbooks, glossary). When a memory note matures, promote it.
* **Claude Code's own session memory** — Claude Code maintains a separate per-user memory at `~/.claude/projects/<encoded>/memory/`, hidden from the team. nyann does not manage that; this folder is the team-visible counterpart.
* **Secrets** — this folder is committed like any other.
* **Long-form research** — that goes in `../docs/research/`.

## Conventions

* Free-form Markdown. One file per topic.
* If a memory note grows up (large, structured, referenced from elsewhere), promote it to `../docs/` and delete the memory note.
* This folder is intentionally in the repo so every contributor sees the same team-visible "what we're holding in mind" state.

## How this fits

nyann's documentation has three knowledge layers:

| Layer | Purpose | Loaded by AI |
|---|---|---|
| `CLAUDE.md` (repo root) | Router into Project Memory | Every conversation |
| `docs/` (Project Memory) | Durable, structured knowledge | On demand, via CLAUDE.md links |
| `memory/` (this folder) | Ephemeral team-shared scratch | When explicitly read |

For the full Project Memory model, see nyann's documentation principles
(`docs/principles/documentation.md` if you've scaffolded one, otherwise
the [nyann project](https://github.com/thettwe/nyann)).
